overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too
  generic. The agent embarked on a comprehensive design overhaul, starting with
  a new sleep-themed color palette, introducing subtle background elements, and
  redesigning key UI components like progress bars, cards, checkboxes, radio
  buttons, and sliders. The intro section was transformed into a more engaging
  welcome experience with feature cards. During this process, a React console
  error related to  values being passed to input fields was identified and
  fixed by modifying the  component to safely handle such values.
  Following an initial review, the user provided feedback on remaining aesthetic
  inconsistencies, particularly in alert colors and the varied gradients used
  for card headers in the report section. The agent then implemented further
  refinements, creating custom alert utility classes in the global CSS and
  standardizing all report section card headers to a single, cohesive
  sleep-themed gradient. This iterative approach ensured a polished, calming,
  and professional visual experience for the sleep health application.
